-- list-filter-crystal.cell: filter even numbers from a list
-- Tests: list filtering, crystallization

⊢ filter-evens
  given numbers ≡ [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]
  yield evens

  ∴ Filter «numbers» to keep only even numbers.

  ⊨ evens = [2, 4, 6, 8]

⊢ crystallize
  given §filter-evens
  given filter-evens→evens
  yield §filter-evens', is-faithful

  ∴ Read «§filter-evens». It filters even numbers.
    Write a ⊢= expression: filter(numbers, n -> n % 2 == 0)
    Return crystallized definition and faithfulness check.

⊢ verify-crystal
  given §filter-evens'
  given crystallize→is-faithful
  yield approved

  ∴ Check: does «§filter-evens'» produce [2, 4, 6, 8] for [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]?

  ⊨ approved = true
